name: JCLAP: Java Comand-Line Argument Parser
summary: JCLAP is a utility for Java developers to help provide a simple and robust command-line interface for software applications which don't require a graphical user interface (GUI). This version is just a minor update release providing simpler use of enumerated string types.

name: DBPool: Database connection pooling for Java  (discontinued)
summary: Java connection pooling library DBPool has just been updated to version 7.0.2 as a small bug fix release. Existing users are recommended to upgrade when possible, but bear in mind that the library has now been officially discontinued, and no new major versions are planned for release.
